<F P=100> Northeast Asia </F>
<H3> <TI>   DPRK Sets Up New Mission at Panmunjom </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    DPRK Sets Up New Mission at Panmunjom </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   OW2505125394 Beijing XINHUA in English 1146 GMT 25 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> OW2505125394 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing XINHUA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Seoul, May 25 (XINHUA) -- The Democratic People's 
Republic of Korea (DPRK) has notified "the United Nations 
Command (UNC)" that it has established "the Korean People's Army 
Representative Mission at Panmunjom" to replace its component of 
the Military Armistice Committee, a UNC spokesman said here 
Wednesday. 
  The DPRK's Army Lt. Colonel Yu Yong-Chol made the 
notification on Tuesday at Panmunjom in his capacity as chief 
liaison officer for the newly-organized mission when he 
contacted UNC Lt. Colonel R. Flury. 
  Pyongyang, however, told the UNC that it will maintain its 
telephone lines at the joint duty officers' room at Panmunjom. 
  The spokesman said that the UNC plans to ask the DPRK to 
hold 
a senior secretaries' meeting of the Military Armistice 
Committee soon to discuss the issue. 
  The DPRK unilaterally withdrew its representatives from the 
Military Armistice Committee on April 27, demanding the Korean 
armistice agreement signed at the end of 1950-1953 Korean war be 
replaced by a peace accord. 

</TEXT>

