  [Text] Beijing, May 26 (XINHUA) -- A five-member delegation 
from the Chinese Supreme People's Court led by its 
Vice-President Ma Yuan left here today for Rome. 
  The delegation will attend an international conference of 
women judges, at the invitation of the International Association 
of Women Judges and the Association of Italian Women Judges. 

