<F P=100> West Europe </F>
<H3> <TI>   NPC Delegation Meets Portuguese Official </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    NPC Delegation Meets Portuguese Official </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   OW2505034294 Beijing XINHUA in English 0254 GMT 25 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> OW2505034294 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing XINHUA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Lisbon, May 24 (XINHUA) -- President of the 
Portuguese Assembly Barbosa De Melo said here today that the 
rapid development of China was of great significance not only to 
China itself but also to the whole world. 
  He made the remarks at a meeting with a visiting Chinese 
delegation headed by vice-chairman of the Standing Committee of 
the National People's Congress (NPC) Wang Guangying. 
  De Melo spoke highly of the great progress China has made in 
recent years in the economic field, particularly in agriculture. 
  Both sides expressed satisfaction with bilateral relations 
and with their cooperation concerning Macao. 
  Macao is now enjoying a period of smooth transition thanks 
to 
the Sino-Portuguese joint declaration on Macao, and people are 
confident about its future, said De Melo. 
  The cooperation between China and Portugal on Macao should 
be 
viewed as an example in solving outstanding problems through 
cooperation between countries, said Wang. 
  At a separate meeting the same day, the Chinese delegation 
held talks with the economic, financial and planning committee 
of the Portuguese assembly on strengthening cooperation between 
the two parliaments. 
  The Chinese delegation arrived here on Monday. 

</TEXT>

