<DOCNO> FBIS4-51346 </DOCNO>
<HT>    "drchi103_n_94010" </HT>


<HEADER>
<AU>   FBIS-CHI-94-103 </AU>
Daily Report 
<DATE1>  27 May 1994 </DATE1>

</HEADER>

<F P=100> Economic &amp; Agricultural </F>
<H3> <TI>   Shanghai B-Share Index Sets `New Record High' </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Shanghai B-Share Index Sets `New Record High' </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   OW2705103894 Beijing XINHUA in English 0940 GMT 27 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> OW2705103894 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing XINHUA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Shanghai, May 27 (XINHUA) -- The index of B-shares 
on the Shanghai Stock Exchange climbed to a new record high to 
close at 71.98 points Thursday, up 1.25 points compared to the 
close of the previous trading day and 4.81 points higher than 
last week. 
  Four B-shares -- Lujian, Refrigerator, Lianhua and Shangchai 
-- topped today's five highest-rising stocks on the exchange, 
ranging from 4.21 percent to 7.14 percent, while the index of 
A-shares witnessed a continuous drop. 
  Experts here attribute the rise of B-shares, exclusive to 
overseas holders, to the better macro-economic situation China 
witnessed from January to April. 
  They pointed out that price hikes basically alleviated in 
April and the rate of foreign exchange remains stable. Foreign 
exchange reserves grow steadily and bank savings are soaring. 

</TEXT>

