<F P=100> TAIWAN </F>
<H3> <TI>   Council Lifts Ban on Group Tours to Mainland </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Council Lifts Ban on Group Tours to Mainland </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   OW2705011194 Taipei Voice of Free China in English 0200 GMT 
26 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> OW2705011194 </F>
<F P=104>  Taipei Voice of Free China </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The Taipei Association of Travel Agents told its 
members on Wednesday [25 May] that group tours to Mainland China 
are being resumed immediately. 
  To protect the interests of its members, the association 
said 
that it has won the permission from the cabinet-level Mainland 
Affairs Council to lift the ban on group tours to the mainland. 
The association reminded its members they should register their 
mainland tours with tourism bureau to complete the legal process. 
  Nevertheless, a number of mainland destinations continue to 
be listed as areas of high risk, and local travel agencies will 
not organize tours heading for such places, including the 
infamous Chientao [Qiandao] Lake in eastern mainland province of 
Chekiang [Zhejiang]. 
  Thirty-two people including 24 Taiwan tourists, six crew 
members, two mainland guides were robbed and burned to death in 
a pleasure boat ride on Chientao Lake March 31. 

</TEXT>

